BCTR Vocabulary Sheet

Term	Canonical Definition
Coordinate	Location of failure or uncertainty
Debt	A missing crossing preventing progress
Entry Debt	No stable starting point
Continuity Debt	Cannot connect to prior knowledge
Transformation Debt	Cannot change representations
Reconstruction Debt	Cannot rebuild from anchors
Return Debt	Cannot reliably revisit later
Bridge Packet	Intervention designed to pay a debt
Crossing	Stable independent performance, explanation, and return
Pressure	Cognitive load associated with a rung
Rung	A stable learning state
Monitor	Learner uncertainty
Break	Ladder uncertainty
Discovery	Map uncertainty
Stable	Crossing achieved and validated

Notes

These definitions are canonical within the BCTR Protocol.

All implementations, schemas, databases, examples, diagnostics, and documentation should use these definitions consistently.

When conflicts arise between representations, the canonical definition takes precedence.

The purpose of this sheet is to prevent semantic drift and ensure that protocol objects remain stable across implementations and over time.
